'''Aurora Glacier''' ({{coord|77|37|S|167|38|E|type:glacier_region:AQ_source:GNIS|display=inline,title}}) is a large [[glacier]] draining that part of [[Ross Island]] between [[Mount Erebus]] and [[Mount Terra Nova]], and flowing south into [[McMurdo Ice Shelf]]. It was named by A.J. Heine in 1963 after the ''[[SY Aurora|Aurora]]'', the ship of the [[Ross Sea Party]] of the [[Imperial Trans-Antarctic Expedition|British expedition]] under [[Ernest Shackleton]], 1914&ndash;17.
