'''Commuted cash value''' refers to the [[present value]] of an [[Annuity (financial contracts)|annuity]] after annuitization. This differs from typical [[cash value]]; if a ''commuted'' cash value is stipulated in an annuity contract, this allows the owner of the annuity to cash the contract in, even after annuitization.<tt><ref> {{cite web|url=http://hcopub.dhs.state.mn.us/hcpmstd/19_25_30.htm |title=19.25.30 Annuities |accessdate=2008-05-05 |date=2006-12-01 |work=Health Care Programs Manual |publisher=Minnesota Department of Human Services }}</ref></tt>

